Agreed and documented information requirements for the theme.

Dataset: Identifiable collection of data. A dataset is a structures collection of (digital) information which describes certain common properties of entities using an agreed set of attributes and standards

The Thematic Common Conceptual TCM (Logical) Model. This is the model that describes: - the concepts and relationships in the domain that are to be represented in the suite of information products - how the information products are related and remain coherent Describes the domain model from an information system perspective. For FSDF we will be using the ISO profile of UML (ISO19103 + ISO19109) (need link) and use elements of the ISO 19100 Harmonized Model This is necessary to ensure that the suite of products within the theme will fit together. The difference between this model and the Business Model is not always clear. However a good rule of thumb is that if you find yourself discussing types (strings, ints, etc) in the Business Model you've slipped into Logical Modelling. This model is the lowest common denominator that is able to encompass existing models (ie. stakeholder models). It is developed from existing implementation models and then tested against the Business Model to ensure it reflects the concepts there.

National Foundation Dataset: A dataset that is aggregated or derived from component datasets and identified as a critical part of the national foundation framework. This dataset is focused on the national scale and there may/or may not be similar jurisdictional datasets held within each jurisdiction
Statement of aspirational information goals of the theme.

National Dataset Aggregator for the FSDF: An agency or organisation that aggregates a National Foundation Dataset from component data sets. This agency or organisation may either be the custodian or a third party aggregator who performs the role under contract or agreement. A National Dataset Aggregator would receive acknowledgement of their position and guidance on their role by the chair of ANZLIC The Spatial Information Council on behalf of the council and the National Dataset Custodian. Contribution Expected: Participation in working groups

FSDF Program Board: Meetings monthly. Program boards role is the coordination oversight of the program implementation actions of OSP and the ANZLIC Secretariat. Membership: The roles within OSP and GA currently occupied by Helen Owens and Simon Costello.

Coordination Advisory Committee: An advisory committee that meets quarterly and comprises of industry bodies, jurisdictional representatives, research bodies participating in the FSDF and the program board. This body is largely focused on the provision of support and advice to the project as well as championship within their respective communities of interest. Membership: SIBA, SSI, Program Board, AIIA, Contact Officer Reps.

FSDF Policy and Coordination Group: Provides an ongoing coordination mechanism for the FSDF sponsors and program board. Twice yearly meeting in person to ensure that the FSDF reporting and leadership is coordinated and evolving. Membership: theme sponsors, program board, FSDF Secretariat

FSDF technical Advisory Committee: An advisory committee that meets monthly and includes Commonwealth Representatives to the OGC , ISO and Standards Australia as well as NICTA, CSIRO and CRC-SI. This group will provide ongoing research, development and technical advice to the Program Board and thematic working groups on the evolution of the datasets.

Theme Working Group: Meetings Fortnightly (tele, email, in person as decided by working group). TWG is focused on technical consultation, work plan implementation, coordination and ongoing evolution of the datasets. Duplication of effort between the FSDF and ICSM will be avoided by close ongoing engagement between groups. ICSM: There may be the ability for modifications to ICSM membership and reporting frameworks to undertake FSDF roles within some themes. Membership: leadership group, data set custodians, key users, key suppliers, aggregators. Members may apply or be invited if users/suppliers or are invited if custodians/aggregators

National Dataset Aggregator for the FSDF: An agency or organisation that aggregates a National Foundation Dataset from component data sets. This agency or organisation may either be the custodian or a third party aggregator who performs the role under contract or agreement. A National Dataset Aggregator would receive acknowledgement of their position and guidance on their role by the chair of ANZLIC The Spatial Information Council on behalf of the council and the National Dataset Custodian. Contribution Expected: Participation in working groups

for the FSDF: An agency or organisation identified as being responsible for the development and management of a National Foundation Dataset, and who has the right to determine the condition applying to the use, distribution and composition of the National Foundation Dataset. The National Dataset Custodian would be responsible for the ongoing evolution of datasets as defined by itself and the thematic working groups. Their role would comprise the development and delivery of their National Foundation Dataset and the maintenance of a close working relationship with thematic sponsors to ensure that yearly vision statements are achieved. A National Dataset Custodian would be invited to the position by the chair of ANZLIC The Spatial Information Council on behalf of the council. Contribution Expected: 2 hours per week (Staff participation in working groups and documentation work). $15k each year for the FSDF technical evolution fund of the design level elements of the Framework. Technical evolution could include increased quality of data, increased efficiency in supply chains, modelling of datasets to better meet customer demands, standards implementation or new delivery mechanisms.

Key FSDF Supplier: A key FSDF supplier is a critical supplier of data to a National Foundation Dataset. A key FSDF supplier may be from the Commonwealth, a Jurisdiction or local government or the private sector and would be identified for their key role by a sponsor or custodian. A FSDF supplier may apply for membership to a working group or be invited by the Theme Sponsor or Dataset custodian. Contribution Expected: Participation in working groups

Key FSDF User: A key FSDF user is a consumer of a National Foundation Dataset as an input to solve problems and /or make decisions. A key FSDF user may be from the Commonwealth, a Jurisdiction or the private sector and would be identified for their key role by a sponsor or custodian. A FSDF user may apply for membership to a working group or be invited by the Theme Sponsor or Dataset custodian. Contribution Expected: Participation in working groups

National Dataset Aggregator for the FSDF: An agency or organisation that aggregates a National Foundation Dataset from component data sets. This agency or organisation may either be the custodian or a third party aggregator who performs the role under contract or agreement. A National Dataset Aggregator would receive acknowledgement of their position and guidance on their role by the chair of ANZLIC The Spatial Information Council on behalf of the council and the National Dataset Custodian. Contribution Expected: Participation in working groups

An agency or organisation (Commonwealth or Jurisdictional) having a special interest in ensuring that the National Foundation Datasets within a particular theme are widely available and of high quality. The agency/organisation must have the structure and resources to enable it to provide leadership, in conjunction with the Office of Spatial Policy, to a number of National Dataset Custodians covering a range of National Foundation Datasets. Their role will include liaising with other national sponsors, consulting a community of users and coordinating activities with custodians to ensure foundation datasets are delivered and evolved in accordance with the wider ANZLIC direction and in conformance with standards, specifications and user priorities. A National Theme Sponsor would be invited to the position by the chair of ANZLIC The Spatial Information Council on behalf of the council. Contribution Expected: Each theme sponsor would be expected to provide an in-kind staff member to act as a working group facilitator. It is envisaged that this position would on average contribute 2 hours a week to the project.

FSDF Secretariat: Will provide ongoing coordination of the administrative elements of the FSDF. The secretariat will hold reporting templates, manage the FSDF Policy and Coordination Group and assist in the management of meetings of the TLG and TWG. The Secretariat will collate and deliver theme vision and update reports to the council. To avoid duplication the FSDF secretariat will be collaboration between OSP and ICSM to take advantage of established frameworks where possible. Contribution Expected: Coordination and administration of the program. This will include facilitating leadership group meetings, managing the evolution fund, providing assistance to sponsors in the facilitation of working groups and managing the reporting framework.
